A merry wight was he:<br/> 
'If London Tower were Michael's hold,<br/> 
We'd set Trelawny free!<br/> 
'We'll cross the Tamar, land to land:<br/> 
The Severn is no stay:<br/>
With "one and all," and hand in hand;<br/> 
And who shall bid us nay?<br/>

